<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-60-0254 </DOCNO><TEXT>It is suggested that the US is more than a swing supplier of coal - itis an integral part of a world coal market which is coming to value thesecurity, reliability and flexibility of US coal supply. US shipmentsfor the first half of 1988 have grown by 9%, production has increased,and the entire coal chain has been strengthened by ongoing improvementsin ports and harbors. Brief discussion is presented of coal exports fromother countries, and conditions are compared with those of the USA.</TEXT></DOC>